<subSubSection pageId="114" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="114.[189,310,1775,1801]" box="[189,310,1775,1801]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1775,1801]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1775,1801]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="114.[189,1399,1822,2027]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thuy, 2013" authorityName="Thuy" authorityYear="2013" box="[322,472,1822,1848]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiogaleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,472,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Ophiogaleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[481,590,1823,1849]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with relatively small LAPs displaying moderately coarsely meshed stereom on outer surface; up to ten spine articulations on strongly elevated distal edge proximally sharply bordered by undulose ridge; three poorly defined spurs on outer proximal edge paralleled by up to four well-defined spurs on inner distal edge in proximal LAPs; single large, well-defined spur on outer proximal and inner distal edges in median to distal LAPs; ridge on inner side of LAPs with strongly widened dorsal part with conspicuously pointed dorsal and ventro-proximal angles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
